        <abstract>
            <p>Encloses reviews by Asa Gray and Bronn. Comments on Bronn review. Mentions review by Wollaston.</p> 
<p>Comments on paper by W. H. Harvey in <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi> [(1860): 145–6]. Discusses Harvey’s belief in the permanence of monsters.</p> 
            <p>Discusses CL’s objection that still-living primitive forms failed to develop.</p> 
<p>The survival of <hi rend="italic">Lepidosiren</hi> and other primitive types of fish and mammals.</p> 
        </abstract>
